RAM is volatile Memory
HDD/SSD is non volatile Memory


Types of files:
1. Text Files(.txt,.c,.py etc)
2. Binary Files (.jpg , .dat etc)

Using Python we can read,update and delete files.These functions are built in


# We have to open the file before doing anything,
# open('filename','mode')      mode signifies what to to do with file
# default mode is r=read if not specified by user
 Other Modes
# w= writing
# a= appending
# += updating
# rb = open in binary mode
# rt= open in text mode   (this is same as just 'r')